commits.commitMessage:
Fix missing builds in pipeline jobs

When there are some parallel builds, sometimes the links would
appear in the same line like:
  Starting building: XStarting building: Y
(where X and Y are links to respective jobs).

So far only the first link was being analyzed, resulting in part
of the build not being analyzed.

That's a bit complex for what it does.
If anything you could declare ms in the 'intervals' above and only chose to display it if duration < 10s

Something like

commits.commitMessage:
Parse 'section' logs + info about queueing duration

Provided a function that parses the log of freestyle jobs to
retrieve info about 'sections'.

A section is a log in the form of:
[section:<name>] start type=<type> time=<timestamp>
[section:<name>] end time=<timestamp>

For instance, it looks like:
[section:git-clone] start type=scm time=1527237016
[section:git-clone] end time=1527237026

This allows to represent what's happening inside a build even
though it is just a script.

This also adds a representation of the time spent in the queue as provided
by the https://github.com/jenkinsci/metrics-plugin/ plugin.

Resolves: FARM-1623
Change-Id: Ib6d161bdc9cdf54edfebc2535909318e2044cbd1
commits.subject: Parse 'section' logs + info about queueing duration
